data.message: Isn't the shutdown supposed to save money?

The shutdown is because there is no authority to continue to spend money.  There's a lot of areas where money is being lost; e.g., loss from business from unavailable infrastructure, e.g. census, BEA numbers being unavailable. (e.g., my company is unable to access census data because of the shutdown). The number is an estimate of how much money will not be added to GDP. By not spending the government is effectively removing money from the system.
